post_text:
Hello NPS Families! This week we began Phase III of our Remote Learning Plan. A few things you/your child can expect: 1. List of assignments, meetings and due dates for the week from each class/teacher. 2. At least two online teaching sessions per week/per core class (either a virtual live classroom or a pre-recorded video of the lesson). 3. A live weekly check-in session (i.e. office hours) with each teacher so students can ask questions, or get more information and guidance.

The goal for this phase of the closure (through the last day) is to ensure that students are learning the critical standards necessary to help them successfully enter the next grade level with a strong foundation.

If you have any questions or concerns about anything during this last phase, please don't hesitate to reach out to your child's teacher(s), the building administrators or me. We are all here to help you and your children work through this crazy time in all of our lives. Be well!

Amy

Hello, NPS Families! I hope you are enjoying some much needed rest and relaxation this week! I am hoping that each of you is able to take a few minutes to complete our NPS mid-year survey. This is the same survey that was sent out at the end of the year last year, so that I could establish some baseline data around what our families felt were the strengths and weaknesses of the district. We have been using your feedback from that survey to help develop our school and district goals, as well as my own personal Superintendent goals. Now, I'd like to measure our progress toward achieving some of the goals we have set, and see where we still have work to do.
Here is the link . . .
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScXIGc6m3iXNK-3eJO_rsplgD5CPQOsBJ8KGwMDllomLM2XiQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

We appreciate your time and feedback! Enjoy the rest of your vacation week. :)

post_text:
The Northbridge School Committee is seeking community input for recommendations to name our new elementary school.

Residents of the town of Northbridge, as well as members of the school community, are invited to submit their name recommendations to the School Committee through Friday, March 22nd. Submissions may be made via the following link on the district website:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfqGJzluihyC-m0en7ZoV0xlk_T46SgllYyToZ3SOs4f_DJAQ/viewform

The community is asked to provide a brief rationale for their name recommendation as well as their name, address, and affiliation with the school district.

The School Committee will review the submissions at its March 26th meeting and create a shortened list of options for consideration. On April 9th, the committee will hold a Public Hearing to obtain community input to the options. The committee will vote to name the new school building at its regular meeting on April 23rd.

post_text:
You are invited to register to participate in a budget input session on Wednesday, January 16 from 6-8PM in the Northbridge High School Media Center.

The goal of this event is to engage community stakeholders in a collaborative discussion about the services and resources they most value in our school system.

In a working session modeled after our Strategic Planning process, stakeholders will engage in a process of articulating budgeting priorities based upon the NPS Strategic Plan. This is not a session to learn about the budget, but rather to assist us in developing a list of vital resources needed to meet our strategic objectives.

The list produced will be presented to the School Committee for their consideration during the budget review and approval process.

Please use this link to register: https://goo.gl/forms/GMfB78Q7Lt6j4Ks72

If you have any questions, please contact the District Office.
